<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" id="lostlesscertain">
	<head>Letters completely lost (extent less certain due to variation in the size of surviving
		characters)</head>
	<ab><rs type="conformance">leiden</rs></ab><div id="lostlesscertain-typographic" type="gl-typographic" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete">
		<head>Traditional typographic representation</head>
		<list type="simple">
			<item><bibl default="NO"><title level="a" type="abbreviated">Panciera</title>, <abbr expan="page">p.</abbr><biblScope type="pages">18</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl default="NO"><title level="a" type="abbreviated">Dohnicht</title>, <abbr expan="page">p.</abbr><biblScope type="pages">4</biblScope></bibl>: <list type="ordered">
					<item id="TypoEx-1">[ - - - ]</item>
					<item>[ - - - - - - - - - - ]</item>
				</list></item>
		</list>
	</div>
	<div id="lostlesscertain-regex" type="gl-regextest">
		<head>Regular Expression Test</head>
		<list>
			<item id="Regex-1">
				<![CDATA[\[\s*((-\s*)+)\s*\] = <gap id="%mkIDgap28" reason="lost" extent="%g1%len2" unit="character"/>
            <certainty target="%mkIDgap28" locus="extent" degree="low"/>]]></item>
		</list>
		<link id="TestLink-1" type="regextest" targets="TypoEx-1 EncEx-1 Regex-1"/>
	</div>
	<div id="lostlesscertain-edition" type="gl-edition" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete">
		<head>EpiDoc appearance with standard XSLT</head>
		<list type="ordered">
			<item id="EncEx-1">
				<gap id="gap28" reason="lost" extent="3" unit="character" precision="circa"/>
				<certainty target="gap28" locus="extent" degree="low"/></item>
			<item>
				<gap id="gap29" reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character" precision="circa"/>
				<certainty target="gap29" locus="extent" degree="low"/></item>
		</list>
	</div>
	<div id="lostlesscertain-notes" type="gl-notes" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete">
		<head>Notes</head>
		<p>Both examples communicate the certain loss of characters, but a significant difficulty in
			determining how many characters are lost, either because the width of surviving individual
			characters elsewhere in the inscription makes estimates difficult, or because the line ends
			are entirely lost.</p>
	</div>
	<div id="lostlesscertain-responsibility" type="gl-responsibility" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete">
		<head>Responsibility for this section</head>
		<listBibl default="NO">
			<bibl default="NO">
				<respStmt>
					<resp>author</resp>
					<name>Tom Elliott</name>
				</respStmt>
			</bibl>
			<bibl default="NO">
				<respStmt>
					<resp>author</resp>
					<name>Gabriel Bodard</name>
				</respStmt>
			</bibl>
		</listBibl>
	</div>
	<div id="lostlesscertain-cvs" type="gl-cvs" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete">
		<head><abbr expan="Concurrent Versioning System">CVS</abbr> Information</head>
		<p id="lostlesscertain-cvs-revision-number">Revision number: <seg n="cvs-revision-number" cert="high" part="N">$Revision$</seg></p>
		<p id="lostlesscertain-cvs-revision-name">Revision name (if any): <seg n="cvs-revision-name" cert="high" part="N">$Name: not supported by cvs2svn $</seg></p>
		<p id="lostlesscertain-cvs-revision-date">Revision date: <seg n="cvs-revision-date" cert="high" part="N">$Date$</seg></p>
		<p id="lostlesscertain-cvs-revision-author">Revision committed by: <seg n="cvs-revision-author" cert="high" part="N">$Author$</seg></p>
	</div>
</div>
